  "prompt": "Is it okay to donate books to a toy drive?",
  "response": "Donating books to a toy drive can be a thoughtful gesture, but it ultimately depends on the specific guidelines of the toy drive you are considering. Some toy drives may accept books as part of their donations, especially if they aim to provide a variety of gifts for children. However, others may only accept toys. \n\nTo ensure your donation is appropriate, it's a good idea to check the requirements of the toy drive or contact the organizers directly. If they do not accept books, you might consider donating them to a library, school, or literacy program instead.",
